 "SEC-005": {
  "status": "Fixed",
  "date": "2026-06-29",
  "commit": "f26c8258",
  "note": "Removed the CorsFilter (CorsConfig.java deleted) entirely instead of tightening it. SPA and API are same-origin in every env (prod/preprod/qa: same host under /api; dev: Angular dev-server proxies /api server-side); all other API callers are server-to-server. With no Access-Control-Allow-Origin emitted, browsers block all cross-origin requests by default - strictly stronger than an allowlist and eliminates the credentialed-wildcard CORS. Spring Security does not use .cors() and nothing referenced the bean."
 },
