 "SEC-011": {
  "status": "Fixed",
  "date": "2026-06-29",
  "commit": "d1674251",
  "note": "Deleted APIInvokeLogAspect entirely (it existed only to dump request/response bodies, leaking JWT/reset-token/PII to logs). It was ad-hoc, scoped to just 5 consumer controllers, fired only on success (@AfterReturning - no failures/status), and carried a no-op @Around. No code referenced it. Uniform request/access logging + auth-failure monitoring should be handled by a real access log and the SEC-018/019 work, not this aspect."
 },
